 <span data-ttu-id="84366-149">Per ulteriori informazioni sull'utilizzo di <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> classe per definire una grammatica, vedere [creare le grammatiche con GrammarBuilder](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7e2cc577-cb05-4318-9da3-7c8675d3d9ae).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="84366-149">For more information about using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> class to define a grammar, see [Create Grammars Using GrammarBuilder](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7e2cc577-cb05-4318-9da3-7c8675d3d9ae).</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="84366-150">L'esempio seguente crea una grammatica di riconoscimento vocale utilizzando <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Choices> e <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> oggetti.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="84366-150">The following example creates a speech recognition grammar using <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Choices> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="84366-151">Il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.%23ctor%2A> costruttore crea un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> dall'oggetto di <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> oggetto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="84366-151">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.%23ctor%2A> constructor creates a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> object from the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> object.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
// Create a grammar using a GrammarBuilder and return the new grammar.   
private static Grammar CreateGrammarBuilderGrammar()  
{  
  GrammarBuilder builder = new GrammarBuilder();  
  
  Choices cityChoice = new Choices (new string[]   
  {"Seattle", "New York", "Miami", "Los Angeles"});  
  
  builder.Append("I would like to fly from");  
  builder.Append(cityChoice);  
  builder.Append("to");  
  builder.Append(cityChoice);  
  
  Grammar citiesGrammar = new Grammar(builder);  
  citiesGrammar.Name = "GrammarBuilder Cities Grammar";  
  
  return citiesGrammar;  
}  
```

  
  
